:FED.
1. Applications
:SKRSLUT.
.sp 3mm
:SWISS8.
:FED.
1.1 Purchases in shops
:SKRSLUT.
.sp 3mm
Mobile Money is a payment instrument, which can be used for payment of
goods and services in shops that accept Mobile Money. You can only make
purchases for the amount available in the associated account. Purchases can
only be made in Danish kroner (DKK).
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
&BANKNAVN. has set a general maximum limit for use of Mobile Money. This
maximum can be seen when establishing the agreement. The set maximum limit
depends on whether the user is older or younger than 15 years of age. The
account holder may set lower maximum limit than the general maximum limit
set by &BANKNAVN.. In the event of changes to the maximum limit, the
originally concluded agreement will still apply.
.sp 3mm
Mobile Money may not be used for any illegal purposes.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
1.2 Restrictions on use
:SKRSLUT.
.sp 3mm
Mobile Money cannot be used in the situations described in clause 8. If
&BANKNAVN. and/or &BANKNAVN.'s technical centres are involved in a
labour conflict, notification of the start and end of such conflict will be
made as quickly as possible.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
There may be times/periods during the night time where Mobile Money cannot
be used as a consequence of data updates and/or maintenance.
.sp 5mm
.kp off
.kp on
:SWISS10.
:FED.
2. Use of Mobile Money
:SKRSLUT.
.sp 3mm
:SWISS8.
In order to make payments with Mobile Money, the following procedure must
be observed:
.sp 3mm
*¤Follow
.in 5mm nobreak
the instructions from the shop when purchasing goods or services
.in 0mm
.kp off
.kp on
*¤The user
.in 5mm nobreak
will receive a request for acceptance of the purchase as well as of the
size of the amount via e.g. a text message. The instructions from the shop
for acceptance of the purchase must be observed.
.in 0mm
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:KURSIV.
Receipt
:SKRSLUT.
.br
The user will receive a confirmation of the payment transaction from the
shop showing that the transaction has been completed. The receipt will be
sent by text message, by letter, email or another durable medium. The shop
will provide information about how the receipt is sent, when it is not sent
by text message.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
The receipt from the shop will show, inter alia, mobile number, the name of
the shop, amount and date. The user should ensure that the amount is in
accordance with the purchase made. In the event of errors on the receipt,
the shop must be contacted immediately. The receipt should as a minimum be
stored until the account holder has checked the entries in the account.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:KURSIV.
Revocation
:SKRSLUT.
.br
Payments which have been approved by the user cannot be revoked. See,
however, clauses 11 and 12 regarding the possibility of reversing a
payment.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:KURSIV.
Reservation and withdrawal of amounts from the account
:SKRSLUT.
.br
The purchase amount will be reserved in the account once the user has
approved the payment. This means that transactions can no longer be made
using the reserved amount. From the time of &BANKNAVN.'s receipt of the
payment order from the shop, the amount will be withdrawn from the account
no later than the following business day. However, Handelsbanken may at any
time, without incurring liability, refuse to effect payments, transfers,
etc. where the restrictions agreed with &BANKNAVN. are not observed or
where the funds available in the account are insufficient for a transfer.
.br
The reservation will be deleted automatically after 14 calendar days if the
amount has not yet been withdrawn from the account.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:KURSIV
Subscription
:SKRSLUT.
.br
It is possible to pay for subscriptions using Mobile Money. The user must
approve each individual withdrawal. The shop will subsequently request the
user to approve the specific transaction via Mobile Money before the next
payment can be made according to the subscription agreement.
.sp 5mm
.kp off
.kp on
:SWISS10.
:FED.
3. Safekeeping of the mobile phone
:SKRSLUT.
.sp 3mm
:SWISS8.
Please be aware that Mobile Money via the registered mobile phone can be
used for direct withdrawals from the account associated with the Mobile
Money agreement. In order to prevent misuse of Mobile Money, the mobile
phone must be kept so as to prevent others from using Mobile Money.
.br
If technically possible on the mobile phone, a code should be used in order
to prevent unauthorised use. This could e.g. be a key lock with code
digits. The code must not be disclosed to anyone.
.sp 5mm
