10. Check of account entries
:SKRSLUT.
:SKRSLUT.
.sp 3mm
The account holder has a duty to check the entries in the account
regularly. If, upon checking the entries, the account holder discovers
transactions which are not consistent with the transaction receipts or
which the user does not believe to have made, &BANKNAVN. must be
notified as soon as possible. In this respect, please note the deadlines
set out in clauses 11 and 12.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
If the account holder has associated other users, the account holder must
ensure that it is possible to check the transactions made by the associated
users, cf. clause 4.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
In connection with regularly checking the entries in the account, the
account holder must be aware that when using Mobile Money for distance
contracts, the shop is as a general rule not entitled to withdraw the
amount until the product/service has been dispatched or delivered. When
purchasing e.g. bus and train tickets or movie or concert tickets, the shop
will, however, withdraw the amount immediately when the trip is booked or
the ticket is ordered.
.sp 5mm
.kp off
.kp on
:SWISS10.
:FED.
11. Reversal of accepted payments
:SKRSLUT.
:SKRSLUT.
.sp 3mm
:FED.
.hy off
11.1 If the user did not know the final amount upon acceptance
.hy on
:SKRSLUT.
.sp 3mm
If the user did not know the final amount when approving the payment, and
the amount which is subsequently withdrawn from the account is
significantly higher than what could reasonably be expected, there may be a
claim for reversal of the payment.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
The account holder must contact &BANKNAVN. as soon as possible, however,
no later than eight weeks from withdrawal of the amount from the account in
the event that the account holder believes to have a claim for reversal of
a payment for which the user has not accepted the final amount. &BANKNAVN.
will reverse the amount or give a reasoned refusal to the
account holder no later than 10 banking days after contact has been made.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
:FED.
11.2 Distance contracts
:SKRSLUT.
.sp 3mm
If Mobile Money has been used for purchasing products or services by means
of a distance contract, the account holder may be entitled to have a
payment reversed, if:
.sp 3mm
*¤the shop
.in 5mm nobreak
has withdrawn an amount higher than agreed
.in 0mm
.kp off
.kp on
*¤the
.in 5mm nobreak
product/service ordered has not been delivered, or
.in 0mm
*¤the user
.in 5mm nobreak
has used an agreed or statutory right of withdrawal by not
accepting or collecting the product/service ordered.
.in 0mm
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
The user/account holder must first try to solve the problem directly with
the shop before contacting &BANKNAVN.. Documentation of the account
holder or user having contacted or tried to contact the shop is required.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
It is a condition that the account holder contacts and raises an objection
with &BANKNAVN. as soon as possible upon realising that one or more
unauthorised withdrawals have been made from the account. Objections must
to the widest extent possible be raised with &BANKNAVN. no later than 14
days after the account holder having discovered the potential claim. When
assessing whether the account holder has raised an objection with
&BANKNAVN. in due time, importance will be attached to the account
holder's duty to regularly check entries in the account, cf. clause 10.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
&BANKNAVN. will then investigate the objection. While investigation of
the objection is pending, the amount in dispute will normally be credited
to the account. If the objection subsequently turns out to be unjustified,
&BANKNAVN. will once again withdraw the amount from the account.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
If the objection turns out to be unjustified, &BANKNAVN. is entitled to
charge interest as from the date the amount was credited to the account and
to the date it was withdrawn again as well as any fees for procuring
documentation.
.sp 5mm
.kp off
.kp on
:SWISS10.
:FED.
12. Reversal of non-accepted payments
:SKRSLUT.
:SKRSLUT.
.sp 3mm
If the account holder/user believes that one or more payments have been
conducted using Mobile Money, which the user has not accepted, brought
about or made, &BANKNAVN. must be contacted as soon as possible after
the account holder/user has discovered the unauthorised transaction. In the
assessment as to whether &BANKNAVN. has been notified in due time,
importance will be attached to the duty to regularly check entries in the
account, cf. clause 10. In any event, &BANKNAVN. must be contacted
within 13 months of the amount having been charged to the account.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
&BANKNAVN. will then investigate the objection. While investigation of
the objection is pending, the amount in dispute will normally be credited
to the account. If the objection subsequently turns out to be unjustified,
&BANKNAVN. will once again withdraw the amount from the account. If the
investigation reveals unauthorised use by third parties of Mobile Money,
&BANKNAVN. may be entitled to claim that the account holder is liable,
cf. clause 7.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
If the objection turns out to be unjustified, &BANKNAVN. is entitled to
charge interest from the date the amount was deposited in the account to
the date the amount was withdrawn again as well as any fees for procuring
documentation of the transaction.
.sp 5mm
.kp off
.kp on
